==English==
===Adjective===
'''savage''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''more savage''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''most savage''')
# [[wild]]; not [[cultivated]]
# [[barbaric]]; not [[civilized]]
# [[fierce]] and [[ferocious]]
# [[brutal]], [[vicious]]{{,}} or [[merciless]]
#: ''That woman acrross the street died from a '''savage''' murder.''

===Noun===
'''savage''' (''plural'' '''savages''')
# a savage person
# {{colloquial}} a [[defiant]] person
#: ''That José dude is a '''savage''', did you hear how he told Mr. Peterson off?''

===Transitive verb===
'''to savage''' (''[[present participle]]'' '''savaging''', ''[[past tense]] and [[past participle]]'' '''savaged''')
# to [[attack]] or [[assault]] someone or something [[ferociously]] or without [[restraint]]

